use updraft_units::{Area, Length, Mass};

use crate::{AircraftPreset, Polar, Propulsion, Variant, WingspanConfig};

/// The built-in aircraft preset catalogue, sorted by base model name.
///
/// The taxonomy (base models, their build/propulsion variants, and each
/// variant's wingspan configurations) plus the `WeGlide` IDs and fallback
/// handicaps come from the `DAeC` glider handicap list and the `WeGlide`
/// aircraft database. Glide polars, reference masses, wing areas, and
/// empty / maximum take-off masses come from the former `updraft_polar`
/// polar store, attached to a taxonomy leaf when its name matches
/// exactly. Polar-store entries that could not be matched confidently are
/// kept (grouped under their base model where the name matches, otherwise
/// as their own entry) so no polar data is lost; matching them to the
/// right variant is left to later manual curation.
///
/// The remaining fields (wingspan for polar-only entries, water ballast,
/// V<sub>NE</sub> / stall speeds, flap speed ranges, CG limits) are not
/// yet populated. A few entries quote a reference mass above their
/// maximum take-off mass, kept as provided by the source data.
#[allow(clippy::approx_constant)]
#[rustfmt::skip]
